site_name: Town Hall Annexe And Brian Didsbury Centre Development Site
description: Demolition of non-original additions to the rear of the Town Hall Annex and demolition of The Didsbury Centre; refurbishment of the Town Hall Annex and the erection of a two storey roof extension; change of use of the Town Hall Annexe from B1(a) Offices to C3 residential use and A3 restaurant/cafe  at ground floor and erection of two new residential buildings, to provide 185 residential units; landscaping, car and cycle parking and associated works.  This application falls within East Ham Civic Conservation Area.   This application affects the setting of a Conservation Area.   This application affects the setting of the following Listed Buildings: -	Technical College Library ,Barking Road, Grade II -	Town Hall, 324 Barking Road,  Grade II star -	Technical College, Barking Road,  Grade II -	Public Library, High Street South , Grade II  -	Former East Ham Police Station, 4 High Street South , Grade II
site_number: Town Hall Annexe And Brian Didsbury Centre Development Site
